name: Gleann | prehnite earrings
description:
Prehnite is a little known, but very unique stone. The pale celery green, paired with its translucency, is divine. These faceted prehnite stones are simply lovely.

The silver beads used in this piece were hand made by the hill tribes of Thailand. Thai silver beads have a higher silver content that sterling silver and are considered fine silver.

materials : prehnite, thai silver, natural brass

length : 1 1/2 inches

name: Coastal no.11 | Kyanite
description:
Kyanite has been one of my favorite stones since the first time I laid eyes on it. The crystal structure is so interesting; like flat layers of shale, but translucent, in shades of the sea. Four small garnet stones provide contrast, and a single Thai Silver bead adds subtle shine. This piece is perfect when you want to add some drama without feeling overwhelmed by your jewelry.

The last photo is a similar necklace and is for reference only.

Stone : kyanite 
Length : 20"
Chain : natural brass


Because all of the stones I use are natural, there is inherent variation in color, pattern and exact size, making your item one of a kind.

name: Greenhouse no.1 Print
description:
These images were a collaboration with the Home Ground for the Greenhouse jewelry collection. The location was the perfect place to compliment the beauty of the pieces, every square foot of the greenhouse held some kind of botanical magic. In between looks, while the model was being styled, I couldn't help but capture the unique specimens all around us. And so was born this collection of images, great companions to the styled shots of the jewelry, but evoking a whole different kind of magic all their own.


Artist : Megan Boltz

Photographs are printed on high-quality, archival Lasal Photo Matte paper (90 lbs). 

See the last image for the full photograph.

Available in these sizes (size given is the paper size) : 4x6" / 8x12" / 11x17" / 16x20" (16x20" is printed to order, please allow up to two weeks processing time)

Ships in a sturdy tube, ready to gift or to keep.

name: Water no.1 print
description:
Feeling the urge to escape my current surroundings completely, I drove down to Clearwater Beach, FL. I spent every evening photographing the ocean at sunset. Being in front of the ocean was like an automatic calming effect. There's a steadiness and openness that comes over me when I attempt to imagine the scale of myself next to something so massive and incredible. More like a state of mind than an actual place.

Artist : Megan Boltz

Photographs are printed on high-quality, archival Lasal Photo Matte paper (90 lbs).

name: Gingerbread Soap
description:
This warm and spiced soap will bring back memories of autumn and the holidays and would make a perfect stocking stuffer or gift. I combined ginger, cinnamon, allspice, benzoin, cassia and clove essential oils and finished the soap with a beautiful cinnamon swirl.

This long lasting bar will nourish and protect your skin for at least a couple months. Remember to keep it in a soap dish with drainage and it will last and last! 

Each bar is 3.5-4 oz.

name: Citrus Soap
description:
This bright and clean smelling soap is a delight to use. I combined sweet orange, lime, tangerine and mandarin essential oils with just a bit of lemongrass, If you love the fresh smell of citrus fruits, this is the one for you! 

This long lasting bar will nourish and protect your skin for at least a couple months. Remember to keep it in a soap dish with drainage and it will last and last! 

Each bar is 3.5-4 oz.

name: Rosemary Peppermint Soap
description:
A wonderfully astringent and brightly scented soap bar. Made with cucumber peel powder as a skin toner and organic rosemary leaves for gentle exfoliation. Perfect for cleansing and opening pores and an all around refreshing wash.

Handmade cold process soap from Portland Oregon. Made with rainwater and natural and sustainable ingredients.

artist : Roots Soap Co.

Each bar is about 3.5-4oz.

name: Wood + Smoke Soap
description:
Smoky, earthy, a hint of woody sweet. Birch tar essential oil is combined with stimulating Ho Wood and a touch of Camphor and Patchouli for a soap that is gentle and moisturizing to the skin and fabulously refreshing to the senses. Made with Rhassoul clay and shea butter.

Handmade cold process soap from Portland Oregon. Made with rainwater and natural and sustainable ingredients.

artist : Roots Soap Co.

Each bar is about 3.5-4oz.

name: Woodsman Soap
description:
Smell the woods! The essential oils of fir, cedar and camphor make this soap small like a walk in forest, and anise lends a sweet hint along with its powerful deodorizing properties . Even if you are city-bound during the week, it will transport you to your favorite spot in the mountains! Men love this one.

Handmade cold process soap from Portland Oregon. Made with rainwater and natural and sustainable ingredients. 

artist : Roots Soap Co.

All soaps are scented with only pure essential oils and made with rainwater. Each bar is about 3.5-4oz.
